&gt; With lightening fast reflexes, she turned, jumped the ring roped in 
&gt; one leap, and ran towards Maxima. &quot;YOU! You do not raise your voice 
&gt; to me young one. I do not care who you think you are. You will show 
&gt; the proper respect. I am the trainer here. You are the interloper. If 
&gt; you want to play games, then leave and do your programming 
&gt; elsewhere.&quot; she said, growling. Her optics red with fury, and the fur 
&gt; on the back of her neck standing up. &quot;You will learn your place young 
&gt; one. In the pack, there is an order. And in that order, I am your 
&gt; supior officer.&quot;  She took a step back to recompose herself. 
&gt; 
&gt; In a more steady and lightly softer tone. &quot;You, young one are clever, 
&gt; smart and well knowledged. But you have yet to really learn how to 
&gt; use this talent to it&#39;s fullest potential. When you have, then you 
&gt; shall be leader. Untill then, I am still higher ranked. You will show 
&gt; the rank respect if not the bot. Much like Hydras. He has my loyalty 
&gt; and respect. And I shall show that to all who are around me. You will 
&gt; do well to do the same.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; She turned and went back to the ring. Her arm still holding her 
&gt; stomach.
&gt; 
&gt; 

Maxima&#39;s optics glowed. But she would not scrap the bot who just seriously 
insulted her. &quot;It is you who have crossed the line. Hydras deserves my 
loyalty for many reasons. YOU however,&quot; her voice still eriely calm but 
obviously there was hint that she did not appreciate what KitKat just did, 
&quot;underestimate me. I am by NO means young. I would be surprized that you 
would be older than I. Rodimus himself is much younger than I. #2... 
Perceptor has placed ME in charge of Blackstorm. I do believe that you have 
over stepped your bounds. If I am correct, I don&#39;t recall Hydras giving you a 
superior ranking let alone charge. Flicker has charge of this place. As does 
Perceptor. Now... if you will so kindly step aside & allow me finish 
Blackstorm&#39;s programming.&quot; Her crimson optics glared at Kitkat. She knew at 
the beginning that this one would be a problem. She was right. So many 
wanting so much. Sounded far too familiar. Sounded much like Starscream.  

